            <abstract>
                <p>A certain man made a vow to Mary, devoting some incense to her. When his house burned down, everything was destroyed except for the incense. On another day, at the church in the same town, a deacon lit a candle before the icon of Mary. The candle set the curtains on fire, but Mary put it out.</p>
